OCI Co. advanced to a two-week high
in Seoul trading after the German government scrapped plans to
reduce subsidized power prices paid for photovoltaic energy in
July.  South Korea â€™s biggest maker of polysilicon, a main
ingredient used for solar panels, climbed 2.5 percent to 447,000
